The Hon. Mr. Justice Yahaya Abiodun Jinadu is dead. Justice Jinadu died on Wednesday, October 9, 2019 at the age 93 years. Justice Jinadu attended Methodist Boys High School Lagos (MBHS) and was called to bar in 1954. He was Solicitor General of the Federation before being elevated to the High Court Bench in Lagos State in 1973. He was known as a very upright judge who believed very strongly in the independence of the Judiciary. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network He retired on principle from the Bench in 1984.Â  He will be buried in accordance with Islamic rites at Vaults and Gardens Ikoyi at 2pm, today. He is survived by children, amongst whom is Mrs. Olugbolahan Babalakin.